extends ../layout.pug

block head
	title Rules

block content
	h1.board-title Rules
	.table-container.flex-center.mv-10
		table.table-body
			tr.table-row
				td
					p 1. Do #[b NOT] post or request anything illegal in the United States.
					p.rule-clarification Pedophilic content and beastiality is not permitted on our site.
					p 2. Do #[b NOT] post or request NSFW, hardcore or softcore pornography, smut, lewds, any HMOFA/HMOMA/Human on Anthro posts, gore or torture, suggestive/pornographic/explicit/fetishistic art or content.
					p.rule-clarification This rule mostly applies to pornographic content or imagery. By using the site, you agree that you will refrain from posting such content. No pornographic content, whether it's slightly lewd or hardcore is tolerated on this website. Content also refers to text/post messages. Frequently posting messages or artwork that is often sexually gratifying, inappropriate or sexually disgusting could lead to action taken under this rule. This rule applies for content pertaining to any sexuality, homosexual, heterosexual, etc and is in place to keep discussion appropriate.
					p.rule-clarification Unlike other websites, we take #[b "Safe For Work"] seriously, this is not a pornographic or suggestive "adult website". If we feel as if you are posting content that attempts to circumnavigate rules for NSFW with softcore or fetishism it may be grounds for deletion, bans, etc.
					p.rule-clarification Gore, torture and videos or images of people in severe pain are prohibited. This includes "DNB".
					p.rule-clarification The use of AI to camoflauge this content is prohibited.
					p.rule-clarification Cartoon violence is allowed.
					p 3. Do #[b NOT] spam, raid this website, or call for raids against other websites that we don't want any trouble with
					p.rule-clarification Trying to coax us into raiding large or significant imageboards or websites will not be tolerated.
					p 4. Do #[b NOT] advocate for pedophilia or zoophilia.
					p 5. Do #[b NOT] advertise crypto, gambling sites, imageboards or Discord servers.
					p.rule-clarification You may link to imageboards as part of discussion, if they're well known and the content of those sites do not violate our rules. If you link to an NSFW thread on another site for example, we have every right to remove your link and issue a ban or warning.
					p 6. VPNs, Tor and Proxies are #[b NOT] permitted.
					p.rule-clarification Blocking these services is a necessity to prevent illegal or malicious activity.
					p 7. We have the right to moderate users based on their actions on and off of the website.
					p.rule-clarification If off-site illegal or "failtroll" or immoral behaviour comes to light we can ban for you it depending on what site rule you broke off of the site.
					p 8. AI generated artwork and text posts are #[b NOT] permitted.
					p.rule-clarification This site is intended for real human creativity. Using AI to filter or overlay over other's artwork or posting AI artwork of anthros is not permitted and they will be deleted. If you were not aware, or made a mistake, we can understand that.
					p.rule-clarification Basically: If someone makes a drawing, don't AI-ify it. Don't post AI Averi images or AI images of anthros. You may post AI "shitposts" or "memes" of anything non anthro related, like Gigachad, for example, and even Pepe and Baxter. But real human creativity is the most important to this site. Don't AI-generate, draw instead.
					p.rule-clarification Overly long AI generated text responses are prohibited. If we want that, we go to ChatGPT. If it's interesting or worth the discussion then paraphrase or screenshot it.
					p 9. Embedding rulebreaking images via the use of steganography or other tools is forbidden.
					p.rule-clarification Embedding sketchy and unverifiable links such as link redirects or links to downloadable ZIP files which could contain illegal or rulebreaking images, videos or malware is forbidden. 

	h1.board-title Moderation Guidelines
	.table-container.flex-center.mv-10
		table
			tr
				td
					p Below are guidelines how to deal with offenses as a moderator, and what to expect as a user.
					p 1. Permanent ban and deletion of offending content.
					p 2. Blatant NSFW is subject to an immediate ban for 1 week or longer. Goonslop is subject to image deletion and a warning or discussion, with a ban of an hour to 1 day to 1 week if the poster does not listen. If a user is making unironic sexually inappropriate text posts, you may give them warnings and ban them for increasingly longer amounts of time.
					p 3. 15 minute ban with a warning, escalate ban times to 30 minutes, then a day, if spam gets out of hand.
					p 4. Permanent ban with a chance to appeal.
					p 5. Deletion of post or removal / redaction of links using Edit. If advertisement is spammed, then punish under the rule for spam.
					p 6. Permanent ban with a chance to appeal.
					p 7. Permanent ban with a chance to appeal. Only moderate based on the severity of the situation. Do not use this rule as an excuse to ban people just because you don't like them, only do so as a means to protection for the community.
					p 8. 1 hour ban with a chance to appeal. If the poster escalates, 1 day ban, 3 day ban, etc.
					p 9. Moderate depending on the rule that was broken. Delete images with untrusted links in them and ban at your own discretion if the user escalates. Do not download files onto your computer for the sake of verifying if the content linked is safe.
					.edited
						| If you believe a ban is false, appeal it. If you feel your appeals are
						| wrongly denied reach the Admin by email, see 
						| <a href="/faq.html">faq</a>.
						| #[b However], if your email is nonsense that is the end of it.
						| You may also ask for help in <a href="/q/">/q/</a> regarding your appeal.


	h1.board-title Legal Disclaimers
	.table-container.flex-center.mv-10
		table
			tr
				td
					p This site is a fan website that is in no way affiliated with or endorsed by Fiddleafox.
					p All posts are owned by the posters. All posts and images uploaded to the site are of the sole legal responsibility of the poster/uploader.
					p This site is intended for users #[b 16 - 18+].
					p.rule-clarification The content served on this website is not sexual or pornographic, but certain language and mannerisms used by our members may be considered offensive and inappropriate. By using this site, we assume you are of an appropriate age and mind to understand the ramifications of trolling and offensive language.
					p We do not endorse or affiliate with any external or different Averi or Fiddleafox related websites, servers or platforms
					p.rule-clarification Many of those platforms do not share our moral principles and harbour unsavoury individuals.
